<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently if you try and decode a JSON value that contains a comment like:</p>

<pre class="literal">
// comment
{"foo": "bar"}
</pre>

<p>The result is a single string property  (zend_debug::dump):</p>

<pre class="literal">
string '// comment
{"foo": "bar"}' (length=25)
</pre>

<p>It would be nice if Zend_Json were able to identify and strip the "//" and /* */" based comments prior to decoding so that JSON strings with comments would parse as expected.</p>

    </div>
</div>

